{"parentUuid":"2583ee94-cd6e-4c2e-8314-a0e552356780","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aff0c9553677dd11a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AXdnnCFBoCsA67b3RkL6NB","type":"tool_result","content":"src\\logging\\__init__.py:6:redaction processor so a secret or raw PII value can never leave the process\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:16:_REDACTED = \"***redacted***\"\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:36:def _redact_sensitive_fields(\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:41:    This is the centralized PII/secret-redaction control every log call\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:42:    inherits automatically — call sites never redact ad hoc.\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:62:    the redaction/anti-forging processors, and stdlib logging routed through it.\"\"\"\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:71:            _redact_sensitive_fields,\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:92:    redaction and field conventions stay centralized (`code-standards` facade\nsrc\\config\\secrets.py:37:    redaction stay centralized.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:5:Centralized structured logging facade using structlog: request middleware (correlation context), PII redaction processor, and a uniform `get_logger()` entry point for all modules.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:11:| `__init__.py` | `get_logger(service=...)` — returns a logger instance with the given service name; applies PII redaction. Facade entry point for all logging calls. |\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:22:- Imports `structlog` for structured logging and the PII redaction pipeline.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:24:**PII redaction:**\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:25:- The `get_logger` facade applies a redaction processor that scrubs known PII fields from log output.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:26:- Fields redacted: `customer_id`, `api_key_id`, `secret`, `key_id`, `idempotency_key`, and other credential-adjacent data.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:27:- Redacted values are replaced with a placeholder (e.g., `\"<redacted>\"` or a hash).\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:28:- Tested in `tests/test_logging_redaction.py`: ensures no raw `customer_id` appears in any log output.\nsrc\\README.md:16:| `logging/` | Structured logging facade (structlog): request middleware, PII redaction, observability correlation. |\nsrc\\README.md:31:- `logging.get_logger` — centralized structured logging facade with PII redaction. Imported by every module that logs.\nsrc\\observability\\README.md:34:- The `before_send` hook in Sentry's configuration scrubs PII fields (same redaction as structured logging: `customer_id`, `secret`, etc.).\nsrc\\observability\\README.md:52:- Matches the same field list as structured logging redaction.\nsrc\\observability\\sentry.py:26:                    headers[key] = \"***redacted***\"\nsrc\\observability\\sentry.py:31:                    data[key] = \"***redacted***\""}]},"uuid":"7c0c727f-87e1-4e96-aa2f-94d662e14908","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:08:57.994Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2583ee94-cd6e-4c2e-8314-a0e552356780","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
