thods=[\\\"GET\\\",\\\"POST\\\",\\\"PUT\\\"] to include \\\"DELETE\\\" on the app-wide CORSMiddleware (not scoped to /v1/quotas), a grep of tests/ finds zero tests mentioning cors or allow_methods, and it is latent only because settings.py:42 defaults cors_allowed_origins to () — exactly as the candidate states.\"},\n  {\"id\":\"C6\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\",\"evidence\":\"list_quotas_endpoint (src/api/routes/quotas.py:68-75) declares no query-param model, so GET /v1/quotas?customer_id=x returns 200 with the full list (FastAPI silently drops unknown params), whereas every other parameterized endpoint — GET /v1/usage, GET /v1/usage/export, and DELETE /v1/quotas itself — rejects unknown query params with 422 via an extra='forbid' model bound with Annotated[..., Query()]; note requirements.md pins 'filtering' out of scope but says nothing about accepting-and-ignoring unknown params.\"},\n  {\"id\":\"C7\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\",\"evidence\":\"quota_service.py line 6 claims GET 'opens a read-only scoped transaction', but scoped_transaction (src/db/session.py:57-73) takes only api_key_id, has no read-only parameter, and never issues SET TRANSACTION READ ONLY — list_tenant_quotas gets an ordinary read-write transaction.\"},\n  {\"id\":\"C8\",\"verdict\":\"PLAUSIBLE\",\"evidence\":\"The contradiction is real in principle — customer_id is on the central must-redact list (src/logging/__init__.py:30, commented 'personal data class per data-protection-conventions') and field-keyed redaction cannot touch a URL query string — but no capturing sink currently exists (no access_logs block in any infra/*.tf, gunicorn runs without --access-logfile per the Dockerfile CMD) and GET /v1/usage already carries customer_id as a query param, so the exposure is a latent, pre-existing pattern rather than a constructible leak introduced by this diff.\"}\n]\n```\n\nSummary for the caller: C1-C7 CONFIRMED, C8 PLAUSIBLE. Key files: `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (unbounded list), `tests/inte